The paper deals with distance labeling schemes for networks, which is a topic in computer science related to data structures and algorithms. The paper specifically focuses on the concept of highway dimension and introduces a new parameter called skeleton dimension. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DS), Computational Geometry (cs.CG), Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI), Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), or Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) sub-categories of arXiv CS. Among these, cs.DS and cs.CG are the most likely categories as they are directly related to the topic of distance labeling schemes and data structures. cs.NI and cs.SI are also likely categories as they deal with network-related topics. cs.DM is a less likely category, but it is still possible as the paper deals with theoretical bounds on hub set size, which is a topic in discrete mathematics.
